BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-dplyr 
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-ggplot2 
Requires:         R-CRAN-dplyr 
Requires:         R-CRAN-ggplot2 

%description
The main idea of the Local FDR algorithm is to estimate both proportion of
null observations and the ratio of null and alternative densities. In the
case that there are many null observations, this can be done reliably,
through maximum likelihood or generalized linear models. This package
implements this in the case that the null and alternative densities are
Poisson.

